The paper is about a new multi-way join algorithm that aims to improve the efficiency of join processing in databases. This topic falls under the category of database systems (cs.DB). The paper also introduces a new data structure called radix triejoin, which suggests a connection to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). The algorithm involves binary encoding and bit-interleaving, which are techniques commonly used in computer arithmetic and digital logic design, suggesting a connection to computer architecture and digital circuits (cs.DC). The paper also discusses conjunctive queries with inequality constraints, which is a topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). Finally, the paper presents a new proof technique, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM).
